issue.title: Add VS console debug prints to engine
issue.body:
- [x] This contribution adheres to [CONTRIBUTING.md](https://github.com/ni/niveristand-fpga-addon-custom-device/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md).

### What does this Pull Request accomplish?

Add lots of VS console debug prints to all states of the engine
Add CDS to determine whether to make the prints
(accidentally bumps modified files to LV 2020)

### Why should this Pull Request be merged?

Currently only 4x debug prints happen in the engine, and all of these are to the RT System Log.
This adds a decent amount of debug prints behind a CDS to track the CD engine as it initializes, starts, executes, and stops.

### What testing has been done?

Deployed a test asset to a Linux RT controller and observed the console output:
Note:
- removed non-related lines where "..." is present
- VS's normal prints are in bold

**Initializing inline custom devices...**
FPGA Addon Initializing
Opening FPGA Session (download and run bitfile)
Completed opening FPGA Session
Initialized Input DMA Refs
Initialized Output DMA Refs
Completed writing initial scalar values
No Async processes to initialize
Completed FPGA Addon Initialization
...
**Initializing Primary Control Loop...
Running system definition...**
...
FPGA Addon Starting
Started async processes
FPGA Addon Started
**Starting Inline Custom Devices...**
**Primary Control Loop initialization complete.**
Starting first Read from Hardware
Finished first Read from Hardware
Starting first Write to Hardware
Finished first Write to Hardware
**Data Processing Loop started...
Primary Control Loop started...
Shutting down Primary Control Loop...**
...
**Finalizing inline custom devices...**
FPGA Addon Stopping
FPGA Addon Stopped
...

issue.title: Make scripting examples usable on cores with 8 channels
issue.body:
- [x] This contribution adheres to [CONTRIBUTING.md](https://github.com/ni/niveristand-ballard-arinc429-custom-device/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md).

### What does this Pull Request accomplish?

- Rename the config files used by the scripting examples for brevity
- Target channels 0 and 16 (instead of 0 and 24)

### Why should this Pull Request be merged?

These example files were based off of the system test assets, which required 16-channel cores to deploy the resulting configuration. It also requires a physically cabled loopback to get useful data transmitted/received.

This change makes these files more like the User Guide assets: target channels 0 and 16 to work on 8-ch cores and without external cabling.

### What testing has been done?

Executed the automated tests that exercise these scripting examples:
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/31290917/200678786-7a81af51-291c-40d4-b276-8b8c257c2c1f.png)

issue.title: Suppress user event error during shutdown
issue.body:
- [x] This contribution adheres to [CONTRIBUTING.md](https://github.com/ni/niveristand-data-sharing-framework-custom-device/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md).

### What does this Pull Request accomplish?

Suppress an error related to firing a user event during shutdown. The user event is triggered several times during shutdown and the top level VI which created it may have left memory, leading to the user event becoming invalid. This should not impact functionality, as the user event has successfully fired once before the top level VI is closed.

### Why should this Pull Request be merged?

Fixes an annoying dialog that pops up when closing pages.

Add lots of VS console debug prints to all states of the engine
Add CDS to determine whether to make the prints
(accidentally bumps modified files to LV 2020)

### Why should this Pull Request be merged?

Currently only 4x debug prints happen in the engine, and all of these are to the RT System Log.
